portfolio.title: Contemporary living room in wood tones
portfolio.anons: This gallery features beautiful living rooms with hardwood floors. Living rooms shown include a variety of styles such as Mediterranean, rustic, craftsman, transitional, Spanish, Asian, modern, contemporary and traditional.
portfolio.block: Solid hardwood is gorgeous and durable. Since it is milled from a single piece of wood it can be repeatedly sanded and last for decades. Engineered hardwood offers an inner core of wood with an outer layer of hardwood veneer. With an engineered hardwood, one can get the same look and beauty without all of the cost.
portfolio.text: In addition engineered hardwood is more resistant to heat and moisture than solid hardwood flooring. In the picture above the rustic solid European oak wood floors gives this Mediterranean home a more relaxed country vibe. Paired with other neutral colors and a touch of turquoise as accent, this home definitely looks really relaxing. Walls are plain white, and ceiling have accent wooden beams in dark wengue finish. Furniture pieces are mostly upholstered in a light cream color, combined with dark wood stain and some touch of blues on the pillows.

category.description: This interior style is characterized by clean lines, simple shapes and soothing color schemes. It often uses natural materials such as wood, leather and cotton, and furniture and accessories usually feature minimal decor and ornaments.

category.name: Modern
category.description: Modern interior style implies modern design using the latest technologies and materials. It has geometric shapes, clean lines and bright colors. This style often uses metal and glass surfaces, and furniture and accessories can be original and unpredictable.

category.name: Eclectic
category.description: This interior style is characterized by a combination of elements from different styles and eras. It can combine classic and modern elements, different colors and textures to create a unique and inimitable interior. In this style, you can show your individuality and creative approach to design.

category.name: Scandinavian
category.description: This design style originated in the Nordic countries and is characterized by simplicity, minimalism, and a focus on functionality. It often features light-colored wood, clean lines, and a neutral color palette with pops of color in the form of textiles or artwork.

category.name: Industrial
category.description: This style takes inspiration from urban lofts and factories, featuring raw materials such as exposed brick, concrete, and metal. It often incorporates vintage or salvaged items, such as industrial lighting or reclaimed wood, and has a rugged, unfinished feel.

wooden_interiors.title: Wooden interiors
wooden_interiors.subtitle: High Level Design
wooden_interiors.text: We present you the best projects developed by our team of professionals with love and care for customers. The portfolio will allow you to choose the style, wood color, texture, design and arrangement of elements that interest you.

warm_atmosphere.title: We create a warm atmosphere for your holiday
warm_atmosphere.subtitle: Best works
warm_atmosphere.text: The development and implementation of beautiful wood interiors has never been so accessible. Interiors made of wood of various species will make your home cozy and warm, delighting you and your guests.
